## When to Use What

### Use Stimulus Controllers (Preferred)

**For:** Interactive UI components, form enhancements, reusable behaviors

```javascript
// app/javascript/controllers/dropdown_controller.js
import { Controller } from "@hotwired/stimulus"

export default class extends Controller {
  toggle() {
    this.element.classList.toggle('open')
  }
}
```

```html
<div data-controller="dropdown">
  <button data-action="click->dropdown#toggle">Toggle</button>
</div>
```

**Benefits:**
- Organized, reusable
- Automatic lifecycle management
- Works with Turbo
- Easy to test

---

### Use Vanilla JavaScript

**For:** Simple one-off scripts, utilities, non-interactive code

```javascript
// app/javascript/application.js

// Simple utility function
function formatCurrency(amount) {
  return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', {
    style: 'currency',
    currency: 'USD'
  }).format(amount)
}

// One-time setup
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  console.log('App initialized')
})
```

